## <summary>Tillandsias in-VM control daemon (vsock boundary policy)</summary>
## <desc>
## <p>
##   Policy for tillandsias-headless, the Rust daemon that binds AF_VSOCK
##   port 42420 inside the Fedora 44 WSL2 instance and bridges the Windows
##   host tray (via HvSocket) to in-VM podman containers.
## </p>
## <p>
##   Use the interface below to grant container domains (vault, forge, etc.)
##   permission to connect to headless vsock service ports (42430–42499)
##   in Phase 5 (vsock-in-vsock). Do NOT grant connectto on the control-wire
##   port (42420) to any container domain.
## </p>
## </desc>

########################################
## <summary>
##   Allow a container domain to connect to a tillandsias-headless vsock port.
##   Used in Phase 5 for container-agent back-channel vsock connections.
## </summary>
## <param name="domain">The container domain type (e.g. forge_container_t).</param>
#
interface(`tillandsias_headless_vsock_connect',`
    gen_require(`
        type tillandsias_headless_t;
    ')
    allow $1 self:vsock_socket {
        create setopt getopt getattr connect read write recv_msg send_msg shutdown
    };
    allow $1 tillandsias_headless_t:vsock_socket connectto;
')
